/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 7 Mar 2026 22:26:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>9</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58823</s:story_id></item><item><title>West Virginia Places Fifth, Two Mountaineers Claim Bronze at Big 12 Championships</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/7/wrestling-west-virginia-places-fifth-two-mountaineers-claim-bronze-at-big-12-championships</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/7/wrestling-west-virginia-places-fifth-two-mountaineers-claim-bronze-at-big-12-championships</guid><category>Wrestling</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Ian Bush at 2026 Big 12 Wrestling Championships (March 7, 2026)" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/7/VTU02896__1_.jpg" /><br /><br />TULSA, Okla. – Two Mountaineers from the West Virginia University wrestling team placed third as the team secured its highest finish in program history at the 2026 Big 12 Wrestling Championships presented by Allstate at the BOK Center in Tulsa, Oklahoma.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/7/VTU02896__1_.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/7/VTU02896__1_.jpg"><media:title>Ian Bush at 2026 Big 12 Wrestling Championships (March 7, 2026)</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/7/VTU02896__1_.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 7 Mar 2026 22:20:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>18</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58822</s:story_id></item><item><title>WVU Posts Strong Showing at No. 12 Utah</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/7/gymnastics-wvu-posts-strong-showing-at-no-12-utah</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/7/gymnastics-wvu-posts-strong-showing-at-no-12-utah</guid><category>Gymnastics</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="kayla smith" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/7/VVB07153.jpg" /><br /><br />SALT LAKE CITY, Utah – The West Virginia University gymnastics team scored a 195.3 to finish in third place in a tri meet against No. 12 Utah and No. 24 BYU inside the Jon M. Huntsman Center in Salt Lake City, Utah, on Saturday afternoon.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/7/VVB07153.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/7/VVB07153.jpg"><media:title>kayla smith</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/7/VVB07153.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 7 Mar 2026 20:27:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>11</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58821</s:story_id></item><item><title>Kresser’s Walk-Off Grand Slam Evens Series Against Columbia</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/7/baseball-kressers-walk-off-grand-slam-evens-series-against-columbia</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/7/baseball-kressers-walk-off-grand-slam-evens-series-against-columbia</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Brodie Kresser" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/7/WalkoffSalami-22.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Brodie Kresser hit a walk-off grand slam to lift the West Virginia University baseball team over Columbia, 9-5, in 10 innings, Saturday afternoon at Kendrick Family Ballpark. The Mountaineers improve to 9-3 while the Lions fall to 2-6.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/7/WalkoffSalami-22.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/7/WalkoffSalami-22.jpg"><media:title>Brodie Kresser</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/7/WalkoffSalami-22.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 7 Mar 2026 18:23:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58820</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Advance to Big 12 Semifinal with Win over Arizona State</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/6/womens-basketball-mountaineers-advance-to-big-12-semifinal-with-win-over-arizona-state</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/6/womens-basketball-mountaineers-advance-to-big-12-semifinal-with-win-over-arizona-state</guid><category>Women's Basketball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Sydney Shaw" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/6/030626_Big_12_Tourney_Day_3_TL-58.jpg" /><br /><br />KANSAS CITY, Mo. – The No. 15 West Virginia women's basketball team used an 11-0 run in the late stages of the fourth quarter to get past Arizona State, 67-54, in the quarterfinal of the Phillips 66 Big 12 Tournament on Friday night at T-Mobile Center.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/6/030626_Big_12_Tourney_Day_3_TL-58.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/6/030626_Big_12_Tourney_Day_3_TL-58.jpg"><media:title>Sydney Shaw</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/6/030626_Big_12_Tourney_Day_3_TL-58.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 6 Mar 2026 21:45:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>9</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58817</s:story_id></item><item><title>West Virginia Victorious on Senior Night at Hope Coliseum</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/6/mens-basketball-west-virginia-victorious-on-senior-night-at-hope-coliseum</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/6/mens-basketball-west-virginia-victorious-on-senior-night-at-hope-coliseum</guid><category>Men's Basketball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Chance Moore" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/6/Moore-Main.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Honor Huff scored 24 points in his final regular season home game at Hope Coliseum on Friday night to lead West Virginia to a 77-62 victory over UCF and a season sweep of the Knights.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/6/Moore-Main.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/6/Moore-Main.jpg"><media:title>Chance Moore</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/6/Moore-Main.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 6 Mar 2026 22:44:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>4</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58818</s:story_id></item><item><title>Titus Reaches Milestone, Five Mountaineers in Contention for Third at Big 12 Wrestling Championships</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/6/titus-reaches-milestone-five-mountaineers-in-contention-for-third-at-big-12-wrestling-championships</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/202